[SN]TITLE[SN]
Car crashes into Perth barber's shop

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been freed from a car after it crashed into a barber's shop in Perth.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police and paramedics attended the scene of the collision at Archie's Barbers in County Place shortly before 15:30.
The grey Nissan vehicle collided with the left-hand side of the storefront, smashing the shop's window.
A Scottish Fire and Rescue spokeswoman said the man was removed from the vehicle and taken to hospital.
